gate: OPEN
task: S75-TA1
title: Fix Settings Store Reference Crash (Root Cause)
description: |
  ROOT CAUSE of settings being completely broken:

  File: src/components/language-selector.tsx — line 20
    `const updateSetting = useAppStore(state => state.updateSetting)`

  `updateSetting` does NOT exist in useAppStore. It only exists in useSettingsStore.
  useAppStore returns `undefined` for this selector, and calling it on language
  change throws a TypeError at runtime, breaking the entire settings screen.

  Fix steps:
    1. In language-selector.tsx: replace
         `import { useAppStore } from '@/store/useAppStore'`
         `const updateSetting = useAppStore(state => state.updateSetting)`
       with:
         `import { useSettingsStore } from '@/store/useSettingsStore'`
         `const updateSetting = useSettingsStore(state => state.updateSetting)`

    2. Verify settings-screen.tsx itself mounts without error:
       - useSettingsStore.fetchSettings() must be called on mount ✓ (already there)
       - Confirm /ws/user/settings/getmain returns 200 when token is valid
       - If API returns 401/500, surface error to user (not silent fail)

    3. Add error boundary or isLoading/error display to SettingsScreen:
       - If settings.isLoading → show skeleton rows
       - If settings.error → show retry button with error message

acceptance:
  - Opening settings screen does NOT crash the app
  - Language selector can be opened and a language selected without error
  - Language change calls useSettingsStore.updateSetting({ locale: code }) successfully
  - Settings screen shows loading state while fetchSettings() is in flight
  - Settings screen shows error + retry if API fails

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 1.5 hours
